laboratory_examinations.findings: Positive for protein, trace positive for ketones; sediment contained moderate numbers of bacteria and a few uric acid crystals, without red or white cells.
Hematocrit 46.3%, white-cell count 24,900/mm³ (94% neutrophils, 3% lymphocytes, 2% monocytes, 1% eosinophils), platelet count 444,000/mm³.
Prothrombin time normal; partial-thromboplastin time slightly low at 22.0 seconds.
Total cholesterol 64 mg/dL (1.7 mmol/L), high-density lipoprotein cholesterol 16 mg/dL (0.4 mmol/L), low-density lipoprotein cholesterol 27 mg/dL (0.7 mmol/L), triglycerides 107 mg/dL (1.2 mmol/L).
Aspartate aminotransferase 27 U/L, lactate dehydrogenase 1619 U/L; levels of conjugated and total bilirubin, alanine aminotransferase, amylase, creatine kinase, and alkaline phosphatase were normal.
Sodium level 138 mmol/L, potassium level 4.4 mmol/L, chloride level 93 mmol/L, carbon dioxide level 26.7 mmol/L.
